
Topics

  Recap: Fonts, Icons, RWD, Bootstrap

  DOM --> Document Object Model 
    1. document.createElement
    2. innerText vs innerHtml
          innerText = renders everything as a simple innerText
          innerHtml = renders the parsed value on the right hand side
            ( i.e, <h1>Sam</h1> ---> Header Tag with content Sam )

    3. style ---> element.style.color = 'red', element.style.fontSize='32px', setAttribute --> element.setAttribute('id', 'my-btn');

    4. getElementById  / getElementByClassName
        getElementById --> Selects the first occurence of the getElementById
        getElementByClassName ---> Selects all the elements with matching class


    5. querySelector / querySelectorAll  ---> document.querySelector(".my-class");
        querySelector ---> Selects the first occurence of the matching query
        querySelectorAll ---> Selects the all the occurence of the matching query
    
    6. input example, 
    7. appendChild / append*
        appendChild can only append( put inside an element ) one single child
          returns appended-child
        append can append( put inside an element ) multiple childs
          returns nothing
